@Anneinak Updated 20201115;  I commented below about the positive cases aboard Sea Dream 1 and the potentially negative consequences this would have on the resumption of cruising from Continental US. Judging by this report - https://bit.ly/3kHqFzb - it appears that a Senator a Representative have written to CDC and requested the reimplementation of the no sail order.  @Anneinak Further to my last forecast of 20201112, Carnival has cancelled all US sailings until 31 December 2020, see https://bit.ly/35ulv4R, and hence my revised forecast.  My revision with a 5% allocation prior to 15 January 2021 is based on
i) Carnival Cruise LIne still lists 10 sailings that could take place prior to January 15, 2021. See https://bit.ly/3njXC68
ii) I am assuming that a 'mock' voyage to comply with CDC's conditional sailing order would in fact comply with the question as it is written. The number of positive Covid-19 cases on SeaDream 1 (see forecast 20201112) which docked at Barbados has now increased to 7 (see https://cnn.it/3lJ3XaQ) as of 20201113. Nonetheless, it appears that demand for cruising is still reasonably strong judging by requests to join 'mock' or 'simulated' cruises which are part of he CDC's conditional sailing requirements. See https://cnn.it/3kueOUY.
